    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get that, but it feels like there are these hidden costs or something eating away at my progress. like, why does it feel like the interest is almost working against me to keep the balance high? is there a specific part of the math that makes it feel so heavy at the start?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It feels heavy at the start because, when your principal balance is very high, the interest charges for that month are also very high, even if your payment stays the same. Essentially, a larger balance means more interest accrues before any of your payment even starts making a dent in the original debt. Think of it like this: a big pile of rocks (the principal) generates a lot of \"weeds\" (the interest) each month, and your payment has to deal with those weeds before it can start moving the whole pile.",
      "source": "target",
