      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "While the mechanism itself isn't inherently predatory, the high starting balance *feels* that way because the interest compounds on a large amount. To get ahead of this, you need to aggressively target the principal, which is often done by making extra payments above the minimum required amount. Even small, consistent extra payments can significantly reduce the principal faster, which in turn lowers the base on which future interest is calculated.",
      "source": "target",
